27/03/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Sali Berisha has received a letter from European Commission (EC) President Jose Manuel Barroso, stressing EU expectations for a "constructive political consensus" on reforms and the EU integration agenda.
According to a government press release Saturday (25 March), Barroso confirmed that the EC has asked the EU Council to formally endorse the Stabilisation and Association Agreement with Tirana.
At the same time, he stressed that the country would be expected to show implementation progress for years, before moving further towards EU membership.
He cited fighting corruption, strengthening of administrative capacities and freedom of the media as priorities.
(Albanian News - 27/03/06;
Albanian Government Web site - 25/03/06)
